value `⟪x, a y⟫_ℂ`. Check that
`⟪x, cfcHom ha f y⟫_ℂ = (toComplexMeasure (toResolutionOfIdentity ha) x y).integral f`, and infer 
that it holds for all Borel/continuous functions. Apply it to the identity map.
cf. Rudin "Functional Analysis" Theorem 12.21, Theorem 12.22.
-/
